OL,3,CCash-strapped council plans to axe
OL,4,Clollipop ladies and men
OL,6,FAll lollipop ladies and men may be
OL,7,Faxed across Bristol under city council
OL,8,Fplans to save money.
OL,10,FBristol City Council are proposing to
OL,11,F"remove funding" from school crossing
OL,12,Fpatrols from April as part of its
OL,13,Fannual budget.
OL,15,FThe local authority currently face a
OL,16,F#52 million funding gap over the next
OL,17,Ffive years. Scrapping lollipop patrols
OL,18,Fwould save the council #314,000 a year.
