OL,3,CCash-strapped council plans to axe
OL,4,Clollipop ladies and men
OL,6,FIt decided to keep only school
OL,7,Fcrossing patrols at locations where
OL,8,Fthere was not a traffic light crossing
OL,9,For a zebra crossing already.
OL,11,FCouncillors from opposition parties
OL,12,Fhave said scrapping lollipop ladies
OL,13,Fand men could put children at risk.
OL,14,FStatistics show that children from the
OL,15,Fpoorest households are 28 times more
OL,16,Flikely to be killed in roads compared
OL,17,Fwith better-off youngsters.
OL,19,FBristol Labour group leader Cllr Tom
OL,20,FRenhard said: "One serious injury on
OL,21,FBristol's roads is one too many.
